Project 03

Load and Download the Data

sname <- "toronto"   # put the name of the dataset from the project page here
docs <- dsst_project_docs("revs", sname)
anno <- dsst_project_anno("revs", sname)

Project Code

anno %>%
  inner_join(select(docs, -text), by = "doc_id") %>%
  dsst_pca(doc_var = "user_name", n_dims = 2) %>%
  dsst_kmeans(n_clusters = 2) %>%
  ggplot(aes(v1, v2, color = factor(cluster))) +
    geom_point() +
    theme_void()

anno %>%
  filter(upos %in% c("NOUN", "ADJ", "VERB")) %>%
  inner_join(select(docs, -text), by = "doc_id") %>%
  dsst_pca(doc_var = "biz_category", n_dims = 2) %>%
  dsst_kmeans(n_clusters = 2) %>%
  ggplot(aes(v1, v2, color = factor(cluster))) +
    geom_point() +
    geom_text_repel(aes(label = biz_category), show.legend = FALSE) +
    theme_void()

docs_cluster <- anno %>%
  inner_join(select(docs, -text), by = "doc_id") %>%
  dsst_pca(doc_var = "biz_category", n_dims = 2) %>%
  dsst_kmeans(n_clusters = 2) %>%
  mutate(train_id = "train") %>%
  mutate(doc_id = biz_category)

anno_cluster <- anno %>%
  inner_join(select(docs, doc_id, biz_category), by = "doc_id") %>%
  inner_join(docs_cluster, by = "biz_category", suffix = c("_orig", ""))
dsst_metrics(anno_cluster, docs_cluster, label_var = "cluster") %>%
  filter(count > expected) %>%
  group_by(label) %>%
  slice_head(n = 25) %>%
  summarize(token = paste0(token, collapse = " ")) %>%
  getElement("token")
